-- England’s Finn Is Out of Second Test Against India, Sky Reports
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-11-20T14:58:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-20/england-s-finn-is-out-of-second-test-against-india-sky-reports.html
Fast-bowler Steven Finn has been
ruled out of England’s second cricket Test against India by a
thigh injury, Sky Sports reported, citing coach  Andy Flower .  Finn, who missed the nine-wicket defeat in the first Test
at Ahmedabad, will have a second scan tomorrow to assess the
injury. England is also without Ian Bell, who’s returned home
for the birth of his first child.  The second Test starts in three days in Mumbai.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  